> It's hard to beat the homey, comforting goodness of a shepherd's pie. Our chefs whipped up a vegetarian version that's just as rich and hearty as the original! Meaty mushrooms (in lieu of traditional ground beef) are simmered with tomato paste, veggie stock, and a bounty of fresh veggies and thyme. On top, swoops of creamy mashed potatoes are sprinkled with white cheddar, then broiled to create an irresistibly cheesy crust. Seriously, who needs the meat when you've got all that?!

== White Cheddar Mashed Potatoes ==

Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch pieces; place in a large #pot with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to #pot. Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

== Mushroom & Herb Filling ==

While potatoes cook, trim and quarter @Button Mushrooms{8%ounce}. Trim, peel, and finely dice @Carrots{6%ounce}. Halve, peel, and dice half the @Yellow Onion{1} (whole onion for 4 servings). Strip half the @Thyme{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems (all the leaves for 4); mince leaves.

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} in a medium, preferably ovenproof, #pan over medium-high heat (use a large, preferably ovenproof, pan for 4 servings). Add mushrooms and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, ~{5%minutes}.

Add a drizzle of olive oil to pan, then stir in carrots, diced onion, and salt. Cook, stirring, until veggies are softened, ~{5-7%minutes} more.

Stir @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) into pan with veggies until melted, then add minced thyme, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, and @Flour{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @Tomato Paste{1.5%ounce} until incorporated, ~{1%minute}.

Pour in ¾ cup water (1 cup for 4) and @Veggie Stock Concentrate{3}, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer and cook until sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season generously with @pepper{} and pepper. Turn off heat.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture now to a baking dish.

== Assembly ==

Mash drained potatoes with @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, half the @White Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup} (you'll use the rest in the next step), and @Butter{2%tablespoon} (3 TBSP for 4 servings) until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat broiler to high.

Once filling has thickened, spoon mashed potatoes on top. Spread potatoes into an even layer, leaving a 1-inch border around edge of pan.

Sprinkle potatoes with remaining cheddar.

Broil shepherd's pie until cheese is lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Let rest at least ~{5%minutes}, then divide between plates and serve.